I would suggest this place to the younger crowd or the people who want to go out with friends or that new someone and take them dancing. The service is fast even during peak hours. Closes late for those who are night dwellers. It's one of the inner city night clubs that most likely don't attract tourists but where you'll find locals and service members. It's not one of the fancier night club that you might find in Waikiki. More along the lines of the rustic vibe but with good music, dancing and alcohol.  Now the parking is street, if you can find one, and a lot a few minutes down the street. Pay to park of course. The neighborhood might be a bit unnerving to some but it is safe. Just remember to stay with a group or friend for safe measures. And any driving service can pick you up right outside the venue so there's no need to go to far from the crowd.  For those wanting a little night life of fun, dancing and responsible drinking this is a great place to head to.  Mr. Carlyle

Terrible bar. I ordered a Jameson on the rocks, figuring I would start with something I knew and then branch out. To order I had to yell my order to the waitress 3 times before she heard me because the music was so loud. Finally she heard me and I got my drink. What I was expecting: Jameson with the large cube ice cube like my friends got in their old fashions. What I got: a cheap plastic cup with overflowing ice cubes and a tiny bit of Jameson in the bottom.  For a self proclaimed whiskey bar I figured they could handle pouring whiskey and putting an ice cube in it. Apparently not. I love whiskey and have had a lot of it. But I will never have a drink of any kind from that bar again.

Manifest gets packed! It is a cute bar across from one of my favorite restaurants. We went to kill time until seats opened up and I found my favorite bitters. Mozart Chocolate. They were in a drink called Lefthand. I fell in love. I found I had to keep stopping by for a Lefthand during my travels in Honolulu. They have a great whiskey menu. Hope to visit again!
